<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="alternative-n">alternative <strong><em>n</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /ɔːl'tɜːnətɪv/    美 /ɔːl'tɜːnətɪv/  </p>
<p>[C]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>选择；供选择的东西</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Minibuses with seats for 12 passengers offer an <strong>alternative to</strong> expensive taxis and crowded public transport. 
相对于昂贵的出租车和拥挤的公共交通工具，12座的小公共汽车提供了另一种选择。</p><footer>外研④ – 2</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>In pursuing a dream, we might focus on only one way of making it come true, forgetting that there may be alternatives.
追求梦想时，我们可能会只聚焦于实现梦想的一种方式，而忘记也许还有其他的选择。</p><footer>2011 北京书面表达</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="have-no-alternative-but-to-do-sth">have no alternative but to do sth</h3>
<p>1.<strong>除了做某事别无选择：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I had no alternative but to report him to the police. 
除了向警察举报他，我别无选择。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">派生词汇</h2>
<p>alternatively /ɔːl'tɜːrnətɪvli/ adv   </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I could come to your house, <strong>or alternatively</strong> we could meet in town.
我可以来你家找你，或者我们也可以在城里见面。</p></div></div>